claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A table listing influenza virus strains (A(H1N1)pdm09, A(H3N2), B/Victoria, B/Yamagata lineages) and amino acid differences in the HA head domain at specified positions for cell-derived, egg-derived, and egg CVV viruses across two years. does not support the claim because the table shows amino acid differences between egg- and cell-derived vaccine candidate viruses but makes no reference to Flublok or its antigenic matching to WHO- or FDA-selected strains. Note: The image quality is sufficient to see that Flublok is not mentioned; the table focuses on egg- versus cell-based CVVs, not recombinant HA match assurances.
